Concordia Virtual Tour++ transforms the existing static 360° campus view into a fully interactive WebGL app powered by 3D Gaussian Splatting, letting users freely navigate and explore Concordia’s grounds. An integrated AI chatbot (via a Hugging Face model) answers questions about the university or your current scene.

3D Gaussian Splatting Pipeline: Capture images → COLMAP reconstruction → train Gaussians → load into a WebGL viewer with navigation & collision detection.

AI Chatbot: Swap in any sub-10 MB Hugging Face model via its URL and set your API key.

Origins & Thanks:
Built in 24 hrs for ConUHacks IX, leveraging Antimatter15’s WebGL Gaussian Splat viewer and the foundational research on real-time Gaussian Splatting.

A summer‐long robotics showcase blending real‐time AI vision, embedded control, wireless comms and custom hardware:

AI‐Powered Auto‐Aiming Cannon: Python + OpenCV/Mediapipe + YOLOv8 on Hugging Face for live target detection and PID-tuned motor actuation.

FPV Head-Tracked Turret & Tank Steering: I²C gyros feeding C++/Arduino code for smooth camera control and non-linear drive algorithms.

Custom Radio & Remote: NRF24 SPI packets in C++ for low-latency RC, paired with a 3D-printed, integrated antenna and power-managed handheld unit.

Marshmallow Launcher & Power Electronics: 3D-printed magazine cannon (4–5 m range) plus a ground-up buck converter PCB with RVP/OVP and adjustable output.

Core skills span Python, C++, PCB design, 3D modeling/printing, AI vision stacks, and real-time embedded systems.

DND-Game is a CMake-built, Dungeons & Dragons-style RPG featuring:

Default Campaign: Three progressively tougher levels to explore and conquer.

Map Editor: Design and save your own battlegrounds (map loader coming soon).

Character Creator: Craft and customize your hero before adventuring.

Options & Audio: Tweak gameplay and sound settings via the main menu.
